{
  "moduleId": "AHDSR",
  "notes": "EcoMode parameter is vestigial - the setter is a no-op (comment: 'not needed anymore'). Downsampling is now controlled globally by HISE_CONTROL_RATE_DOWNSAMPLING_FACTOR (8x for instruments, 1x for effects). The envelope state machine lives in ahdsr_base::state_base::tick() shared with the scriptnode equivalent. All curve shapes use exponential coefficients, not lookup tables. AttackCurve controls the attack target ratio (concave to convex), DecayCurve controls the decay/release target ratio. The sustain phase in calculateBlock() uses a per-buffer ramp when the sustain value changes (via modulation), avoiding zipper noise. Monophonic mode uses a single shared state with optional retrigger behavior.",
